post_text:
Due to a staff member testing positive and it being so late in the day we will have all students go remote learning for Friday, September 18, 2020. This will give us the opportunity to clean and conduct our contact tracing. Lunch will still be available to anyone that wishes to have it. Please let us know by 8:30 tomorrow morning and it will be ready to be picked up at noon.
Teachers and staff members will still come in at 8:00 to disinfect and help determine who, if anyone, will need to quarantine.
The game against Mullin scheduled for tomorrow evening is still going to happen unless something else comes up.

I sincerely apologize for the certain inconvenience this presents but it's what I felt was necessary for the safety of all those involved.
If I can answer any questions please do not hesitate to call the school. Have a good evening.

Dwin Nanny

DON'T FORGET!
If your child is returning to Panther Creek CISD, whether you plan for them to learn remotely (from home) or attend in person, you must register them on line.
If you have used our ParentPortal before, to check grades, please go to the ParentPortal https://panthercreek.txeis15.net/ParentPortal/login?distid=042905, and log-in. Then in the left-hand column click on "SUMMARY" next click the word "Registration" under your child's name. Please complete all information and submit.
** If you can not click on the word "Registration" go to settings and see if your email address is up to date and change if needed. If you still can not click on "Registration", contact the school.
***If you have NEVER used our Parent Portal set up a new account and contact the school for the student ID code when you reach that point.

Senior Spotlight!!
We are proud of you!

Shila Woodcox

Congratulations and good luck!

My name is Shila Woodcox. My love for animals has always played a major role in my life. I’ve always wanted to help and care for all I could no matter the breed. My mother would ask what I wanted to be when I grew up, and when I said a Vet Doctor who helps exotic animals, she always said she could tell it would have to do with animals. I will attend college online for the first semester. Following college, I will have achieved a degree in Veterinary and as a Marine Biologist. I am excited to see my hopes and dreams come to life. The future is endless with possibilities.



I would not have been able to accomplish this much in my life without the help of my parents, family, teachers, counselor, principal, and the remaining faculty and staff at Panther Creek. The love and warmth I have been shown, has strengthened me as a person, and given me the desires and drive to reach for the stars.

Panther Creek FFA
March 19 at 4:06 PM ·

Parents and Guardians:

As we navigate through these circumstances surrounding the COVID-19 spread, students will be receiving all assignments online. A Google classroom has been created for your student with information on each assignment to be completed. Google Classroom can be accessed via https://classroom.google.com/ or the Google Classroom App can be downloaded on any smartphone, iPad, etc.

Each student has been invited to their respective Google classroom using their school email address. All assignments for each class will be completed on iCEV. post_text:
Hurricane Battle

To help provide supplies to White Oak High School (see article above), we are holding a "Battle of the Classes". Between October 19th and November 2nd each grade Pre-K thru 12 will be trying to raise as much cash as possible. This money will then be used to buy supplies from the Amazon account listed below to help White Oak High School in N Carolina.
There will be two local winners in this competition. The top Elementary class (Pre-K-5th) and the top secondary class (6th -12th) will each win a pizza party.
If you would like to contribute to this fund raiser, give your money to any Panther Creek student or bring it with you to our Fall Festival on October 27th.

TEA released the accountability ratings for districts to the public today. Panther Creek doesn’t receive a letter grade this year because we are a single campus district. PCCISD did receive a rating of “Met Standard”, with a score of 85 out of 100. We are very proud of our staff and students and the hard work and effort they put forth everyday.
Ratings can be found at www.txschools.org.
It’s a great day to be a Panther!
